    "body": "@Aniket-Engg thanks for getting back to me, the path was inside the share folder. \r\n\r\nThe structure of the project looked like this:\r\n\r\n- contracts/abstracts/SomeAbstract.sol <-- here we have the `import \"../interfaces/Context.sol\";`\r\n- contracts/interfaces/Context.sol\r\n- contracts/Main.sol <-- here we import SomeAbstract\r\n\r\nThe command is run from `.` directory where `contracts` folder is. So they are all inside the shared location. It works when you have `./` but `../` for an import breaks it. I had a look at the code. The `../` import was sending it outside the main shared folder, instead of just outside the `abstracts` folder.\r\n ",
